║  MISSION: SHIP LOG VERSION CONTROL                                    ║
║  Location: Bridge - Archives Terminal                                 ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ARIA BACKUP: The ship's document archiving system has failed.         │
│  We need to initialize a new version control system to track           │
│  critical repair logs.                                                 │
│                                                                        │
│  Git is the standard for version control - it tracks changes to        │
│  files over time, allowing you to see history, revert mistakes,        │
│  and collaborate with others.                                          │
│                                                                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

MISSION BRIEFING:

Two critical documents need to be archived:
  • repair_log.md    - Record of all repairs performed
  • system_notes.md  - Technical notes about ship systems

Your task: Initialize a git repository, add these files, and create
a commit to preserve them in the archive.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

GIT BASICS:

  git init              - Initialize a new repository (creates .git/)
  git status            - Show current state (what's tracked, modified)
  git add <file>        - Stage a file for commit
  git add .             - Stage all files
  git commit -m "msg"   - Create a commit with a message
  git log               - View commit history

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

OBJECTIVES:

1. Initialize a git repository in this directory (git init)
2. Stage both files for commit (git add)
3. Create a commit with a message containing the word "repair"
4. Run ./verify to confirm the archive is established

VERIFICATION REQUIREMENTS:
  • .git directory must exist (repository initialized)
  • Both files must be tracked (committed)
  • At least one commit must exist
  • Commit message must contain "repair" (case-insensitive)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

EXAMPLE WORKFLOW:

  git init
  git add repair_log.md system_notes.md
  git commit -m "Archive repair documentation"
  ./verify

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

NOTE: If git asks for your identity, configure it with:
  git config user.email "operator@odyssey.ship"
  git config user.name "Ship Operator"

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
